as he ran his eye over the notes, now smiling, now frowning, and sometimes turning back like a reader checking a detail in a novel — a name, the time of the year. 'It must be a great pleasure,' his father had said, 'to assimilate music in its natural state.' It was a similar pleasure that Luzhin himself now began to experience as he skimmed fluently over the letters and numbers representing moves. At first he learned to replay the immortal games that remained from former tournaments —

